<item>
            <title>[LU-12014] check correct size in ll_dom_finish_open()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12014</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cloned from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11595&quot; title=&quot;sanity-dom sanityn test 11: LBUG: (file.c:470:ll_dom_finish_open()) ASSERTION( lnb.lnb_file_offset % ((1UL) &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 16) == 0 ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11595&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11595&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to capture a related patch being added to that already resolved ticket.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The check in ll_dom_finish_open() for data end shouldn&apos;t use i_size for comparision because it may be not updated yet with just returned data from server. Use size value in mdt_body from reply for that check.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre Build: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/3811&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/3811&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
